Question 1

Read in all 4 credit card transaction datasets and clean column names.

card_base <- read_csv("data/CardBase.csv") %>%
  clean_names()

 Column specification 
cols(
  Card_Number = col_character(),
  Card_Family = col_character(),
  Credit_Limit = col_double(),
  Cust_ID = col_character()
)
customer_base<- read_csv("data/CustomerBase.csv") %>% 
  clean_names()

 Column specification 
cols(
  Cust_ID = col_character(),
  Age = col_double(),
  Customer_Segment = col_character(),
  Customer_Vintage_Group = col_character()
)
fraud_base <-read_csv("data/FraudBase.csv") %>% 
  clean_names()

 Column specification

  Transaction_ID = col_character(),

Question 5

Read in hat_observations and separate observation into two columns, hat_colour and hat_type.

hat_seperated <- hat_observations %>% 
  separate(observation, c("hat colour", "hat type"),
           sep = ",")

hat_seperated

Question 6

Unite day, month, and year columns into a column called date using a suitable separator. Then find the date where the most berets were observed.

hat_separated_unite <- hat_seperated %>%
  unite(date, c("day", "month", "year"), 
        sep = ":")

hat_separated_unite
hat_separated_unite %>% 
  filter(`hat type` == "beret") %>%
  group_by(date) %>% 
  summarise(total = sum(observation_count)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(total))
